        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I saw `--embed --headless` come up when starting to dig into this, not sure if it has the desired effect? IE locally I've got `--embed --listen ...` not exiting immediately when stdio closes. When I start with `--embed --listen ...` and connect from neovim-qt, I see the new error message about not being able to find the SF Mono font.\n\nBut when I start with `--embed --headless --listen ...` I see no such message, implying that neovim did not wait for the client to connect.\n\nAlso not sure if nvrh setting `chan->detach` from nvrh will help. There's an untold amount of time before nvrh connects to the socket, and I definitely want the server to exit once all clients have exited.",
